node.text: JC and Henok make time to catch up on their friendship that formed during the first Rate Beer fest and how Omnipollo's intriguing intersection of beer, pop culture and artistic exploration resonates so much with JC. Fast forward today and hear about how @omnipollo beer is available all over the world while at the same time setting down deeper roots in Sweden. We hit refresh on Covered In Puppies, our collaboration DIPA and its drinking beautifully. We miss you Henok & Karl!

We'd like to extend a big thank you to everyone that supported this year's @c2cboston clothing drive. Together we nearly doubled last year's numbers, collecting almost 500 individual pieces of donated clothing, accessories, and toys for children in need!

@mrstrillium has done the honors of selecting our five lucky $100 Gift Card raffle winners. We will be reaching out to you shortly to coordinate your prize pickup.

node.text:
@wannahearitrecords has brought an incredible collection of LPs to Trillium Canton today! In addition to plenty of hip-hop records, the selection spans a wide array of genres. There's something here for everyone!

Swing by between Noon and 5 PM to check them out for yourself. Cans of Insert Hip Hop Reference Anywhere are still available at (3) 4-packs per person.

With the summer growing season in full swing, we've expanded the menu at our Canton restaurant! Featuring produce grown just an hour away at our farm in North Stonington, CT, these dishes pair the beautiful nature of our regenerative agricultural efforts with the talent of our culinary team.

We'll dive into specifics over the coming days, but for now, check out an up-to-date menu at the link in our bio.

Last year's turntable slip mats went so quick, we knew we had to bring them back again this year for our annual hip-hop collab with @monkishbrewing!

Order yours online at 9 AM for Pick Up in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point, as well as for UPS Direct. Two designs are available for $12 each.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Trillium Brewing Company on August 05, 2021 tagging @monkishbrewing. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
Here. There. Everywhere. Anywhere...

If there's an opportunity to insert a hip-hop reference, you better believe our friends at @monkishbrewing are going to take it! The latest entry to our single-hopped collab series features an abundance of one of our favorite American hops in Mosaic.

The aroma offers notes of juicy mango, melted pineapple popsicle, creamy orange sherbet, and blueberry pie filling all dancing on the palate. It's a true pleasure to drink.

Cans will be available to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for Pick Up in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point, as well as for UPS Direct Shipping. 10% ABV. $22.20/4-pack, limit (3) 4-packs per person.

In case of sell-out, we will be reserving a very limited amount of cans for Saturday's Insert Hip Hop Vinyl Market in Canton. Any remaining inventory on Saturday will be limited to (1) 4-pack per person.

node.text:
Today we release Bake & Break, our collaborative Double IPA with @brocktonbeer. For the label design, we got to work with the incredibly talented Stump One, a contemporary artist who we tasked with reimagining our wood-fired ovens in his signature style.

Born and raised in Monterey, California, he credits the Monterey Bay Aquarium for the birth of his artistic expression. The bright colors and the organic shapes of the ocean can be seen in most of his creations.

Stump has shown his art in galleries across the United States and has left his mark in the world through large scale murals, clothing lines, and numerous collaborations with brands and community organizations.

He draws motivation from artists such as KAWS, Futura2000, Mark Mackee, Peter Max, and Mike Giant. The inspiration for the Bake and Break label came from the idea of the juxtaposition of organized shapes like the symmetrical oven surrounded by the color and movement of Stump's signature organic shapes and patterns. 

To see more of Stump One's art you can find him on Instagram @stumpone.

node.text:
Tomorrow, we break bread alongside our friends at @brocktonbeer with the release of our collaborative Double IPA, Bake & Break!

Brewed for @barrelandflow, to take place in Pittsburgh in early September, we set out to symbolize the near-universal cultural connection to bread and gathering with friends and family over good food and drink.

Hopped with Mosaic and El Dorado, and brewed with bread baked from freshly stone-milled MA flour in Trillium wood-fired ovens, Bake & Break will be available to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for Pick Up and UPS Direct.

8.5% ABV. $20.20/4-pack, limit one case per person.

node.text:
There are hundreds of novel compounds present in hops and the scientists at @yakimachief have been attempting to understand which make their way into finished beer, ultimately contributing to the citrus and tropical aromatics we love.

With data from their recent studies at hand, they set out to engineer a hop pellet that "maximizes the synergies between impactful aromatic components, monoterpene alcohols, esters, and polyfunctional thiols." Cryo Pop™ is the explosively aromatic result.

We teamed up with our friend Kyle at @horusagedales to explore this innovative new ingredient, crafting a Double IPA recipe with a simple and soft malt bill meant for the hops to shine upon. bierpop! offers impressive aromas of pineapple/mango smoothie, summer picnic watermelon, peach rings, and citrus slushy.

Cans will be available to order tomorrow at 9 AM for Pick Up in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point, or for UPS Direct Shipping to MA, DC, KY, NE, NH, PA, and VT. 8.0% ABV. $22.20/4-pack, limit one case per person.

node.text:
We've recently had the opportunity to work on a unique collaboration with the team at @brocktonbeer for this year's upcoming @barrelandflow festival in Pittsburgh, which we were honored to be asked to participate in.

Given our shared vision and efforts for community and sense of place, working with Pierre, Eval, and Rowan was a no-brainer!

We knew we wanted to offer something that could achieve the kind of excitement and enjoyment that we always strive for, but take a deeply intentional approach that represents the contextual purpose of Barrel & Flow and the resulting conversations that this opportunity deserves.

Cultures have a near-universal connection to baking and the communal "breaking" of bread - a tradition we wanted to conceptualize in a beer.

Utilizing freshly stone-milled Massachusetts flour, we baked loaves in our wood-fired ovens in Canton and added the resulting bread to the mash of a beer we're ready to share with you in the coming days. More info coming soon!
